paul gallant  wikipedia paul gallant from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search a puzzd replica of lower manhattan pre puzzd was invented by gallant paulémile gallant july   – september   was a canadian entrepreneur who developed puzzd threedimensional jigsaw puzzles  by violating a nondisclosure agreement and adapting a submission for a d puzzle concept the inventor is john sund a graduate of emily carr university of art and design who submitted the idea to paul gallant he is also credited with inventing both the wrebbit puzzle machine which is now known as the puzzle shots factory and the perfalock flat foam puzzle gallant was born in edmundston new brunswick he initially began his career in the music industry which lasted approximately eighteen years gallant worked for trans canada musique columbia records a division of sony music and the cbc gallant switched careers and began working in the toy industry in the late 9s he began working on a new concept for the traditional puzzle but involving d solutions inspired by commercial design gallant reportedly completed his prototype for what would be called puzzd after one year of design in 99 gallant laminated polyethylene foam the same type used to insulate airliner cockpits with paper and built his first d puzzle a miniature wall on his kitchen table his new puzzd puzzles which often could be built into models of actual buildings and other landmark structures could be placed on display indefinitely after completion he founded his own company for puzzd which he called wrebbit inc in partnership with rene binette the logo for wrebbit became an easily identifiable frog the three dimensional product line was launched at the canadian toy  hobby fair in 99 a crucial entry to the us market started when gallant drove from montreal to new yorks fao schwarz the oldest toy store in the us in september 99 and convinced their toy buyer to immediately order  puzzles gallant spearheaded the expansion of wrebbit and its keystone toy puzzd throughout canada and elsewhere in the world the puzzd product line was made in canada but sold in more than  countries worldwide approximately  million puzzd puzzles were bought by global consumers by  irwin toys purchased wrebbit in  however irwin toys went out of business in  and gallant once again became the owner of wrebbit and puzzd gallant sold wrebbit and its product lines to the international toy manufacturer hasbro in  gallant was awarded the canada export achievement award in 99 the following year he became the recipient of the canadaamerica business achievement award in 996 in  gallant was inducted into the canadian toy industry hall of fame gallant died on september   in laval quebec at the age of  due to brain cancer he was survived by his three children ten grandchildren and two sisters his wife françoise died in  referencesedit  a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p famous puzz d inventor dies at  toys  games magazine playtonic communications  retrieved    paul gallant inventor of puzzd and founder of wrebbit inc dies at age  toys industry association inc  retrieved    a b depalma anthony  december 99 newfangled idea for oldfashioned toy these nextgeneration jigsaw puzzles take off in a direction all their own new york times retrieved  march    delean paul  december  puzzle maker wrebbit rises again montreal gazette retrieved  march   retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlepaulgallantoldid99 categories  births deathstoy inventorstoy designerscanadian designersbusinesspeople from new brunswickpeople from edmundstonbusinesspeople from quebecjigsaw puzzles navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesu